# Truegrynd – UI Design Guidelines

## Brand Identity
- **Vibe**: Raw, street, grit. Anti-luxury fitness. The "Casio G-Shock" of sports apps.
- **Never**: pastel colors, rounded friendly shapes, Instagram aesthetic
- **Always**: Dark backgrounds, high contrast, aggressive typography, sharp edges

## Color Palette (CSS variables in globals.css)
| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--background` | `#0a0a0f` | App background |
| `--primary` | `#dc2626` | CTAs, active states, highlights |
| `--accent` | `#ffb800` | Gold trophies, streak badges |
| `--card` | `#111118` | Card backgrounds |
| `--muted` | `#1c1c28` | Subtle surfaces |
| `--border` | `#2a2a3a` | Borders, dividers |
| `--faction-nomads` | `#4a9e6f` | Nomads faction color |
| `--faction-horde` | `#c0392b` | Horde faction color |
| `--faction-iron` | `#7f8c8d` | Iron Alliance faction color |

## Typography
- Use Geist Sans (loaded via Next.js) for body
- Headlines: bold/black weight, tight letter-spacing
- Numbers (scores, ranks): monospace or tabular nums — `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`

## Layout
- Mobile-first: design at 375px, scale up
- Min touch target: 44×44px
- Dark mode only in MVP (no light mode toggle needed)

## Component States
Every interactive component must handle: loading, empty, error, default, disabled

## Finisher Card
- Generated on canvas (client-side, no server rendering)
- Dark background with faction color accent
- Must show: score value, world rank %, faction emblem, Truegrynd logo
- Export as PNG for native share

## Accessibility
- WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios minimum
- All interactive elements must have `aria-label` or visible text
- `focus-visible` outlines must be styled (never `outline: none` without replacement)
